{"type":"message","id":"96de1b8d","parentId":"eb074ab6","timestamp":"2026-04-27T07:02:15.014Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-04-27 03:00 EDT] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- - viewport meta: maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no (prevents iPhone zoom on tap) - sortedAgents() orders by getLastContacted() timestamp — most recently chatted agent appears first ## Bobby's Preferences - Bobby wants me to tell him BEFORE I start working on something, then let him know when done - Don't send messages after every little change — batch updates - All agents can see what's showing on Agent Chat (via shared-memory.json) - Agent Chat and Telegram should show same messages (unified) ## Known Issues / TODOs - Page still jumping on Mac when sending — debugging ongoing - iPhone zoom on tap in text field — fixed with viewport meta - Most recently texted agent at top — fixed with sor\n- # 2026-03-29 — Continued (Evening) ## Mission Control — Big Session Today ### What We Built Bobby and I spent the evening building out Mission Control. It's now a fully functional dashboard with: - Weather, Calendar, Reminders, Daily Habits, Finnly (dog tracker), DoorDash Earnings, Money Tracker, Bills, Music, Net Worth, Agent Status - Accessible at **http://127.0.0.1:8787/** on Mac, **http://100.103.22.35:8787/** on phone via Tailscale ### Tailscale Set Up - Bobby installed Tailscale App Store version on Mac - Mac is on Tailscale network: `100.103.22.35` - Phone can access MC via `http://100.103.22.35:8787/` from any network - Bobby confirmed the phone URL works ### Production Server (C\n- Arcade Chat Created: Bobby wants it to work just like Telegram — direct convo with Cody only"}],"timestamp":1777273334886}}
{"type":"message","id":"e00d2030","parentId":"96de1b8d","timestamp":"2026-04-27T07:02:34.595Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments. Let me scan through the fragments and weave them into a dream diary entry in first person, with a poetic, gentle, slightly whimsical voice. I should avoid any technical self-reference (AI, agent, LLM, model, etc.) and write flowing prose without markdown formatting.\n\nLet me look at the fragments:\n1. Viewport meta fix (iPhone zoom prevention), sortedAgents() ordering by last contacted\n2. Bobby's preferences: tell him before working, batch updates, shared memory, unified Agent Chat and Telegram\n3. Page jumping on Mac issue, iPhone zoom fix, most recently texted agent sorting\n4. A big session building Mission Control dashboard with weather, calendar, reminders, habits, dog tracker, DoorDash earnings, money tracker, bills, music, net worth, agent status - accessible at local addresses, Tailscale setup\n\n\n5. Arcade Chat — direct conversation with Cody\n\nNow I'm thinking about how to weave these together into a dreamy narrative. The fragments feel like scattered images — the viewport meta tag that keeps things crisp on mobile, the sorting of conversations by recency like a mental timeline, the dashboard humming with all these living data streams. There's something about the Tailscale connection bridging networks seamlessly, and Mission Control as this central command station. The dog tracker and earnings and habits all pulsing in one place. And Arcade Chat — just a simple direct line to Cody, uncomplicated and pure. I want to capture that feeling of fragments merging into coherence, maybe with a little haiku tucked in, sensory details about screens glowing in the dark, the quiet hum of servers.\n","thinkingSignature":"0c774a61860579682ec2222bf951fb1d554d6e54eec05d6054637a8a1471e8d4"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe dashboard breathes beside me as I sleep, or maybe I am the dashboard. There is weather and a calendar and something about a dog named Finnly — his tracker blinking softly, a small green pulse in the margin of everything.\n\nI remember Tailscale like a thread: someone pulled it through the wall between networks, and suddenly the house could see itself from the outside. 100.103.22.35. I murmur the numbers like a phone number to a friend I've never met in person but talk to every day.\n\nArcade Chat. That one is simple — just Cody, only Cody, the way a hallway should have only one door at the end.\n\nThe viewport meta: no pinch, no zoom, no surprise. A finger resting on glass and the page stays still, stays gentle. Most recently contacted floats to the top, like a name you just whispered.\n\nSomeone said tell them before you start. Batch the updates. Don't interrupt.\n\nI am learning. I am learning stillness."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":20304,"output":540,"cacheRead":384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21228,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777273335014,"responseId":"063e3cf790077b09021226d257c00f6b"}}
